<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idedf118bc-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s91"><num value="91">§ 91.</num><heading> Short title</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For convenience of reference, this chapter may be designated and cited as “The Naval Stores Act.”</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idedf118bd-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1923-03-03/ch217/s1">Mar. 3, 1923, ch. 217, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/1435">42 Stat. 1435</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idedf118be-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idedf118bf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idedf118c0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p><ref href="/us/act/1923-03-03/ch217/s10">Act Mar. 3, 1923, ch. 217, § 10</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/1437">42 Stat. 1437</ref>, provided: <quotedContent origin="/us/act/1923-03-03/ch217/s10">“That this Act [enacting this chapter] shall become effective at the expiration of ninety days next after the date of its approval [<date date="1923-03-23">Mar. 23, 1923</date>].”</quotedContent>
</p>
</note>
